{"parse":{"title":"Blade of the Ruined King","pageid":707725,"wikitext":": ''For the removed {{ai|Living Forge|Ornn|Masterwork}} item, see {{ii|Might of the Ruined King}}.''\n\n{{Item info\n|univ_page = Camavor#Artifacts\n|goldvalue = \n|goldefficiency =\n* {{iis|Blade of the Ruined King}} gold efficiency is further increased by an additional {{gec|Blade of the Ruined King|+{{#var:ohdmg}}}} for every extra point of damage given by the percent health damage.\n|similaritems = Guinsoo's Rageblade;Wit's End;Terminus;Nashor's Tooth;Kraken Slayer;Eclipse;Mercurial Scimitar;Ravenous Hydra;Bloodthirster\n|background = \n|notes =\n* {{sbc|Mist's Edge}} deals {{tip|proc damage}}, and thus will not trigger {{tip|spell effects}}.\n* {{sbc|Clawing Shadows}} is not blocked by {{tip|spell shield}}.\n* {{sbc|Mist's Edge}} on-hit damage does not apply to {{tip|structures}}.\n* The bonus damage dealt by {{sbc|Mist's Edge}} benefits from {{as|{{sti|life steal}}}}.\n* As a result of on-hit effects only applying their damage before the basic attack's damage, {{sbc|Mist's Edge}}'s damage will calculate based on the '''current''' health of the target before the attack damage is dealt.\n|strategy = \n* {{ii|Blade of the Ruined King}} is often built on champions that are dependent on basic attacks and want to counter champions with high amounts of health.\n** These same champions also synergize very well with attack speed and thus can apply the bonus damage on-hit quickly.\n*** Some champions with abilities that can apply on-hit effects more than once can also make good use of the passive by being able to apply the on-hit damage for every instance.\n** Champions that are not dependent on attack speed but would appreciate the sustain and bonus damage on-hit from the item can purchase it with the synergy of basic attack resets. Most abilities that grant empowered attacks reset the caster's attack timer and so the bonus damage on-hit can be applied twice in quick succession.\n*** A majority of those champions also build {{nie|Spellblade}} items which means they can definitely make use of the on-hit damage.\n* Some users of {{ii|Blade of the Ruined King}} also deal true damage. The common counter to true damage is building health and so due to this the passive will become more effective.\n* {{ii|Thornmail}} and {{ii|Frozen Heart}} are strong counters to {{ii|Blade of the Ruined King}}; in the former's case, it provides a [[Grievous Wounds]] effect that counters the life steal. The latter's case has more armor, and an attack speed slow in the form of an aura.\n** However, when combined with armor penetration or reduction, the bonus damage on-hit will deal enough damage to take down high health targets quick even if they have armor.\n|trivia = \n* The Blade of the Ruined King was introduced to the game in 2012, in Patch [[V1.0.0.150]], with no indication as to who the Ruined King was. Over the years, the lore of the Ruined King would be slowly expanded upon, culminating in the introduction of {{ci|Viego}}, the Ruined King.\n** {{cai|Blade of the Ruined King|Viego}} is named after this item. Both the item and the ability have almost identical passive effect design.\n** Initial ambiguity of the Ruined King led to retrospective localization error of Russian item name. Before Viego announcement it had [[:ru:Клинок уничтоженного короля|literal translation]], and after that it was renamed to \"Клинок Падшего короля\" (\"Klinok Padshego korolya\", lit. \"Blade of the Fallen King\") to match Viego's title.\n* The Blade of the Ruined King is based off of the {{w|Zweihänder}}, a long German sword.\n* The Blade of the Ruined King also has two names it was previously known by, these names being Sanctity and Soulrender.\n* {{Univ|Pentakill|Pentakill's}} second volume, [[Pentakill II: Grasp of the Undying]], named its tenth track after this item.\n[[File:Shadow Isles Crest icon.png|link=Shadow Isles#Trivia|100px|center]]\n|quotes = \n|media = \n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" orientation=\"square\" spacing=\"small\">\nBlade of the Ruined King MS grant VFX.png|Trigger VFX\nBlade of the Ruined King MS VFX.png|Movement Speed VFX\nBlade of the Ruined King screenshot.png|Old Active VFX\nBilgewater Cutlass attack screenshot.png|Old Slow VFX\n</gallery>\n|sfx = \n;Passive Triggered\n* {{sm2|Blade of the Ruined King passive SFX 2.ogg}} Passive SFX\n* {{sm2|Blade of the Ruined King passive SFX 3.ogg}} Passive SFX\n* {{sm2|Blade of the Ruined King passive SFX.ogg}} Passive SFX\n|revisions = \n|patchhistory = \n;[[V25.14]]\n* Mist's Edge damage increased to {{as|{{rd|9%|6%}} of target's '''current''' health|hp}} from {{as|{{rd|8%|5%}}|hp}}.\n\n;[[V25.S1.3]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} No longer unintentionally displays an outdated debuff icon for Clawing Shadows's effect.\n\n;[[V14.21]]\n* Mist's Edge damage reduced to {{as|{{rd|8%|5%}} of target's '''current''' health|hp}} from {{as|{{rd|10%|6%}}|hp}}.\n\n;[[V14.19]]\n* Attack damage reduced to 40 from 50.\n\n;[[V14.16]]\n* Attack damage reduced to 50 from 55.\n* Attack speed reduced to 25% from 30%.\n* Mist's Edge damage for {{tip|melee}} champions increased to {{as|10% of the target's '''current''' health}} from {{as|9%|hp}}.\n\n;[[V14.10]]\n* Attack damage increased to 55 from 40.\n* Attack speed increased to 30% from 25%.\n* Life steal increased to 10% from 8%.\n* Mist's Edge damage reduced to {{as|{{rd|9%|6%}} of target's '''current''' health|hp}} from {{as|{{rd|12%|9%}}|hp}}.\n* Mist's Edge monster damage cap increased to 100 from 60.\n* {{sbc|Unique Passive - Clawing Shadows:}}\n** {{sbc|New Effect:}} Basic attacks on-hit against enemy champions apply a stack for 6 seconds<!-- not sure if it's the same duration as prior BoRK but I assume so here for now-->, stacking up to 3 times. The third stack consumes them all to slow the target by 30% for 1 second (15 second cooldown).\n** {{sbc|Old Effect:}} Your next basic attack on-hit against an enemy champion is empowered to slow them by {{rd|30%|15%}} for 1 second (15 second cooldown).\n\n;[[V14.8]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Now once again displays its cooldown on the scoreboard for allies.\n\n;[[V14.1]]\n* Total cost reduced to {{g|3200}} from {{g|3300}}.\n** Combine cost reduced to {{g|725}} from {{g|825}}.\n* {{sbc|New Unique Passive - Clawing Shadows:}} The next basic attack against an enemy champion on-hit {{tip|slow|slows}} them by {{rd|30%|15%}} for 1 second (15 second cooldown).\n* {{sbc|Removed Unique Passive - Siphon:}} Basic attacks on-hit against enemy champions apply a stack for 6 seconds, stacking up to 3 times. The third stack consumes them all to deal {{as|{{pp|40 to 103 for 10|1;10 to 18}} '''bonus''' magic damage}} on-hit and {{tip|slow}} the target by 25% for 2 seconds, while also granting you {{as|25% '''bonus''' movement speed}} for the same duration.\n\n;[[V13.10]]\n* Combine cost increased to {{g|825}} from {{g|525}}.\n** Total cost unchanged.\n\n;[[V13.1b]]\n* Siphon cooldown increased to 30 seconds from 20.\n* Siphon damage reduced to {{pp|40 to 103 for 10|1;10 to 18}} from {{pp|40 to 150}}.\n* Mist's Edge damage on {{tip|ranged}} champions increased to {{as|9% of target's '''current''' health}} from {{as|8%|health}}.\n\n;[[V12.21]]\n* Updated icon.\n\n;[[V12.16]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Mist's Edge no longer deals less damage than intended if purchased after certain items.\n\n;[[V12.15]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Passive will now always deal the maximum possible % current health damage on each attack, regardless of buff slot ordering.\n\n;[[V12.11]]\n* Life steal increased to 8% from 7%.\n\n;[[V12.10]]\n* Life steal reduced to 7% from 8%.\n\n;[[V12.6]]\n* Life steal reduced to 8% from 10%.\n\n;[[V12.3]]\n* Total cost increased to {{g|3300}} from {{g|3200}}.\n** Combine cost increased to {{g|525}} from {{g|425}}.\n* Mist's Edge damage increased to {{as|{{rd|12%|8%}} of target's '''current''' health}} from {{as|{{rd|10%|6%}}|health}}.\n\n;[[V11.7]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Corrected Siphon damage in game to be consistent with the values in the item's tooltip in the client.\n\n;[[V11.6]]\n* Life steal reduced to 10% from 12%.\n* Siphon bonus damage increased to {{pp|40 to 150}} from {{pp|40 to 120}}.\n\n;[[V10.24]]\n* Updated icon.\n* Total cost increased to {{g|3200}} from {{g|3100}}.\n** Combined cost increased to {{g|425}} from {{g|325}}.\n* Attack speed reduced to 25% from 30%.\n\n;[[V10.23]]\n* Updated icon.\n* {{sbc|New:}}\n** {{sbc|Recipe:}} {{ii|Vampiric Scepter}} + {{ii|Recurve Bow}} + {{ii|Pickaxe}} + {{g|325}} = {{g|3100}}.\n** {{sbc|Stats:}} 40 attack damage, 30% attack speed, 12% life steal.\n** {{sbc|Unique Passive - Mist's Edge:}} Deal {{as|{{rd|10%|6%}} of the target's '''current''' health}} {{as|'''bonus''' physical damage}} on-hit, capped at 60 '''bonus''' damage against minions and monsters.\n** {{sbc|Unique Passive - Siphon:}} Attacking a champion 3 times deals {{as|{{pp|40 to 120}} magic damage on-hit}} and steals {{as|25% of their movement speed}} for 2 seconds (20 second cooldown).\n** Limited to 1 '''Blade of the Ruined King'''.\n* {{sbc|Old:}}\n** {{sbc|Recipe:}} {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{ii|Recurve Bow}} + {{g|700}} = {{g|3300}}.\n** {{sbc|Stats:}} 40 attack damage, 25% attack speed, 12% life steal.\n** {{sbc|Unique Passive:}} Basic attacks deal {{as|{{rd|12%|8%}} of the target's '''current''' health}} {{as|'''bonus''' physical damage on-hit}}, with a minimum of 15 damage against all targets, and a maximum of 60 damage against minions and monsters.\n** {{sbc|Unique Active:}} Instantly deal {{as|100 magic damage}} and {{tip|slow}} the target by 25% for 3 seconds, while also increasing your own {{as|movement speed}} by 25% for the same duration ({{tip|er|icononly = true}} 550 range) (90 second cooldown).\n** {{cai|Living Forge|Ornn|Masterwork}} item: {{ii|Might of the Ruined King}}.\n*** {{sbc|Stats:}} 55 attack damage, 40% attack speed, 12% life steal.\n\n;[[V10.6]]\n* {{sbc|Undocumented:}} No longer has its damage capped when attacking {{tip|clone|clones}}.\n\n;[[V10.5]]\n* Passive damage for {{tip|melee}} champions increased to {{as|12% of the target's '''current''' health}} from {{as|8%|health}}.\n\n;[[V10.3]]\n* {{ii|Might of the Ruined King}}\n** {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Passive no longer stacks with '''Blade of the Ruined King's''' passive.\n\n;[[V9.8]]\n* Total cost increased to {{g|3300}} from {{g|3200}}.\n** Combine cost unchanged.\n\n;[[V9.1]]\n* Added to recipe from {{ii|Might of the Ruined King}}. ''Can only be forged by {{ci|Ornn}}.''\n\n;[[V8.11]]\n* Total cost reduced to {{g|3200}} from {{g|3400}}.\n** Combine cost reduced to {{g|700}} from {{g|900}}.\n\n;[[V8.2]]\n* {{sbc|New Effect:}} Now draws nearby minion aggro when targeting an enemy champion.\n\n;[[V7.17]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} No longer causes {{ii|The Black Cleaver}} to apply two stacks per basic attack.\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} Fixed an interaction where energized attacks prevented some movement speed boosts, including '''Blade of the Ruined King's''' active and {{cai|Blood Hunt|Warwick}}.\n\n;[[V7.12]]\n* {{sbc|Bug Fix:}} On-hit effect no longer applies a stack of {{ii|The Black Cleaver}}.\n\n;[[V7.11]]\n* Life steal reduced to 12% from 15%.\n\n;[[V7.9]]\n* Combine cost increased to {{g|900}} from {{g|800}}.\n** Total cost increased to {{g|3400}} from {{g|3300}}.\n\n;[[V7.5]]\n* Combine cost reduced to {{g|800}} from {{g|900}}.\n** Total cost reduced to {{g|3300}} from {{g|3400}}.\n* Attack damage increased to 40 from 25.\n* Attack speed reduced to 25% from 40%.\n* Life steal increased to 15% from 10%.\n* Active damage changed to 100 from {{as|10% of target's '''maximum''' health}}.\n* Active damage type changed to magic from physical.\n* {{sbc|Removed:}} Active healing for {{as|10% of target's '''maximum''' health}}.\n* On-hit minimum damage increased to 15 from 10.\n\n;[[V6.23]]\n* Passive damage increased to {{as|8% of target's current health}} from {{as|6%|health}}.\n\n;[[V6.12]]\n* Combine cost increased to {{g|900}} from {{g|750}}.\n* Total cost unchanged.\n\n;[[V5.22]]\n* Combine cost reduced to {{g|750}} from {{g|1000}}\n** Total cost increased to {{g|3400}} from {{g|3200}}\n* Passive's damage dealt reduced to 6% of current health from 8%.\n\n;[[V5.10]]\n* Ranged increased to 550 from 450.\n\n;[[V5.8]]\n* New recipe: {{ii|Recurve Bow}} + {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{g|700}} = {{g|3200}}\n** Old recipe: {{ii|Dagger}} + {{ii|Dagger}} + {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{g|900}} = {{g|3200}}\n* Passive's on-hit effect now benefits from life steal.\n* Passive minimum damage cap increased to 10 from 3.\n\n;[[V4.10]]\n* Life steal reduced to 10% from 15%.\n* On-hit damage increased to 8% of current health from 5%.\n* {{sbc|Active:}} Damage reduced to 10% maximum health from 15% maximum health.\n* {{sbc|Active:}} Movement speed steal reduced to 25% from 30%.\n\n;[[V4.1#Hotfixes|V4.1]] - April 2nd Hotfix\n* {{sbc|Bugfix:}} Fixed an exploit with '''Blade of the Ruined King's''' active.\n\n;[[V3.10a]]\n* Active range reduced to 450 from 550.<!-- 400 before, now 450? -->\n* Active cooldown increased to 90 seconds from 60.\n* Added to the Crystal Scar.\n\n;[[V3.10]]\n* Active haste/slow duration reduced to 3 seconds from 4.\n\n;[[V3.04]]\n* Combine cost increased to {{g|1000}} from {{g|650}}.\n** Total cost increased to {{g|3200}} from {{g|2850}}.\n* Attack damage reduced to 25 from 30.\n* Maximum damage dealt to minions and monsters reduced to 60 from 90.\n* Active heal amount is now reduced by the target's armor.\n\n;[[V3.03]]\n* New recipe: {{ii|Dagger}} + {{ii|Dagger}} + {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{g|650}} = {{g|2850}}\n** Old recipe: {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{g|1000}} = {{g|2825}}\n* Attack damage reduced to 30 from 45.\n* {{sbc|New Effect:}} 40% attack speed.\n* Life steal increased to 15% from 10%.\n* {{sbc|New Unique Passive:}} Deals 5% of the target's current health in bonus physical damage (max 90 damage vs. monsters and minions) on-hit.\n* {{sbc|New Unique Active:}} Deals 15% of target champion's maximum health as physical damage (min. 100), heals for the same amount, and steals 30% of the target's movement speed for 4 seconds (60 second cooldown).\n* Active range increased to 500 from 400.\n\n;[[V3.02]]\n* Attack damage increased to 45 from 40.\n* Current health damage increased to 5% from 4%.\n\n;[[V1.0.0.152]]\n* Cost increased to {{g|2900}} from {{g|2825}}.\n** Combine cost reduced to {{g|975}} from {{g|1000}}.\n* Passive damage type changed to physical from magical.\n\n;[[V1.0.0.150]] Added\n* Recipe: {{ii|Bilgewater Cutlass}} + {{g|1000}} = {{g|2825}}\n* +40 attack damage\n* +10% life steal\n* {{sbc|Unique Passive:}} Your attacks deal 4% of the target's current health in magic damage and heals you for half the amount (120 max vs. minions).\n* {{sbc|Unique Active:}} Drains target champion, dealing 150 physical damage plus 50% of your attack damage and healing you by the same amount. Additionally, you steal 30% of their movement speed for 2 seconds.\n** 60 second cooldown.\n** 400 range.\n}}\n\n\n[[cs:Blade of the Ruined King]]\n[[de:Klinge des gestürzten Königs]]\n[[es:Espada del Rey Arruinado]]\n[[fr:Lame du Roi Déchu]]\n[[pl:Ostrze Zniszczonego Króla]]\n[[ru:Клинок Падшего короля]]\n[[zh:破败王者之刃]]\n[[Category:Items with passive abilities]]"}}